Once Initialization is completed, It begins to perform long polling. Updating only the cell values of the table that have been received in long polling.

```
        function long_poll_editorial(){
            var editorial_url = '/data-service/editorial/' + election_date1 + '?options=vote' +"&timeout=30" + "&neat=" + neat1 + "&after=" + global_after;       
            $.ajax({
                dataType: "json",
                url: editorial_url,
                data: {},
                success: function(json){
                    global_after = json.updated
                    console.log(global_after)
                    var races = json.races;
                    for (var i=0; i < races.length; i++){
                        var race_row = document.getElementById(races[i].race_id);

                        $(race_row).find('td#percent_in').html(races[i].percent_in +'%');
                        $(race_row).find('td#candidates').html(get_candidates(races[i]).join("<br />"));
                        $(race_row).find('td#major_party').html(get_candidate_parties(races[i]).join("<br />"));
                        $(race_row).find('td#vote').html(get_candidate_votes(races[i]).join("<br />"));
                        $(race_row).find('td#vote_percent').html(get_candidate_percent(races[i]).join("<br />"));
                        $(race_row).find('td#call_status').html(get_race_status(races[i]));
                        $(race_row).find('td#call_at').html((typeof(races[i].call_at) != "undefined") ? races[i].call_at : "");
                        $(race_row).find('td#call_lead').html((typeof(races[i].call_lead) != "undefined") ? races[i].call_lead : "");        
                        $(race_row).find('td#lead_party').html(getPartyLead(races[i]));
                    }

                    $('#tally_table').trigger('updateAll', [true]);
                    long_poll_editorial()
                },
                error: function(xhr, status, errorReturn){
                    if (errorReturn == "Request Timeout"){
                        console.log("SERVER TIMEOUT RETRY (LONG POLL EDITORIAL")
                        long_poll_editorial()
                    }else{
                        console.log("ERROR LONG POLL: "+ status+" err: "+ errorReturn)
                        long_poll_editorial();
                    }
                }
            });
        }
```

During Long Polling, I issue an `update` or an `updateAll` in order for filters / sort to reapply.

However, When applying `update` the page **always jumps back to the top when the poll is received**

When applying `updateAll` the page **stays where it is, but loses its stickyheader until the page is moved around**

Im a little confused as to why issuing `$('#tally_table').trigger('update')` would cause my page to scroll to top? or why the alternative updateAll would have a different outocome (different UI issue).

